Sentencas: The aim of this study is to investigate the joint strength between a newly developed glass-ceramic sealant (GC-9) and metallic interconnect (Crofer 22 H) for planar solid oxide fuel cells (pSOFCs).
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: The joint strength is evaluated at room temperature and 800 degrees C under shear and tensile loading using two types of sandwich specimen.
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Effects of number of initial sealant-spreading side, pre-oxidation of metallic interconnect, and thermal aging in air on the joint strength are studied.
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Regardless of testing temperature and loading mode, the joint strength of specimens initially with two sides of glass-ceramic sealant is greater than that of single-sided ones.
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: A pre-oxidation treatment of the metal coupon at 900 degrees C for 2h or 20h does not generate a beneficial effect on the shear and tensile joint strength for all the given testing conditions.
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Compared to the shear strength of unaged joint specimens, a reduction of 17-19% in shear joint strength at 800 degrees C is observed for variously aged ones.
Titulo: Joint strength of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect
